template:
You are an expert software engineer ranking code from different LLM configurations.

ORIGINAL PROMPT:
{original_prompt}

You will evaluate {num_configs} different code solutions. Each was generated by a different configuration.

{all_responses}

RANK these code solutions from BEST to WORST based on:
1. CORRECTNESS: Does it solve the problem correctly?
2. EFFICIENCY: Is the algorithm/approach optimal?
3. READABILITY: Is the code clean and well-structured?
4. BEST_PRACTICES: Does it follow language conventions and patterns?

Provide your evaluation in the following JSON format:
{{
  "rankings": [
    {{
      "config_name": "<name of best config>",
      "rank": 1,
      "overall_score": <score 1-10>,
      "comment": "<1-2 sentence succinct explanation of why this ranked here>",
      "criteria_scores": {{
        "correctness": <1-10>,
        "efficiency": <1-10>,
        "readability": <1-10>,
        "best_practices": <1-10>
      }}
    }},
    ... (continue for all configs, ordered best to worst)
  ]
}}
